g.text: Title: Concept for a Uninterruptable Power Supply failure bypass

g.desc: Title: Concept for a Uninterruptable Power Supply failure bypass

g.text: Footpad of the socket of the relay

g.desc: Footpad of the socket of the relay

g.text: Simplified diagram, each line represents a pair of Phase and Neutral.

g.desc: Simplified diagram, each line represents a pair of Phase and Neutral.

g.text: In case of UPS malfunction, the circuit will switch to the power of the Mains (that powers the UPS)

g.desc: In case of UPS malfunction, the circuit will switch to the power of the Mains (that powers the UPS)

g.text: Since the UPS and the Mains source different phases, if the Phase and Netural switches would not

g.desc: Since the UPS and the Mains source different phases, if the Phase and Netural switches would not

g.text: happen precisely at the same time, there would be a chance for mixup and potential problems.

g.desc: happen precisely at the same time, there would be a chance for mixup and potential problems.

g.text: The solution proposed is a two stage double-switching:

g.desc: The solution proposed is a two stage double-switching:

g.text: 1. On the transition from Mains to UPS (UPS working properly):

g.desc: 1. On the transition from Mains to UPS (UPS working properly):

g.text: - The 'Power Switch' will change from Mains line to UPS line, which does not carry electricty yet.

g.desc: - The 'Power Switch' will change from Mains line to UPS line, which does not carry electricty yet.

g.text: - The power to the Mains line is cut off (which triggers the second stage change)

g.desc: - The power to the Mains line is cut off (which triggers the second stage change)

g.text: - The power of the UPS gets enabled

g.desc: - The power of the UPS gets enabled

g.text: - The Mains line gets a second deactivation (useful to prevent abrubt switch in step 2.1)

g.desc: - The Mains line gets a second deactivation (useful to prevent abrubt switch in step 2.1)

g.text: 2. On the transition from UPS to Mains (UPS failure):

g.desc: 2. On the transition from UPS to Mains (UPS failure):

g.text: - The 'Power Switch' will change from UPS line to Mains line, which does not carry electricty yet.

g.desc: - The 'Power Switch' will change from UPS line to Mains line, which does not carry electricty yet.

g.text: - The power to the UPS line is enabled (which triggers the second stage change)

g.desc: - The power to the UPS line is enabled (which triggers the second stage change)

g.text: - The power of the Main gets enabled

g.desc: - The power of the Main gets enabled

g.text: - The UPS line gets a second deactivation (useful to prevent abrubt switch in step 1.1)

g.desc: - The UPS line gets a second deactivation (useful to prevent abrubt switch in step 1.1)
